lity, not just against PECD’s own numbers","position":{"start":{"line":173,"column":1},"end":{"line":173,"column":1}},"key":"i5mETKDZNp"}],"key":"NTPudXLmSq"}],"key":"FOjclOg8s7"}],"key":"bTqETAHORB"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":175,"column":1},"end":{"line":180,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What isn’t built yet, and is deliberately visible as a gap rather than\npapered over: wake-effect/layout correction (step 5 of PECD’s own\nmethodology), curtailment, outages, and behind-the-meter self-consumption\n— none of these have a ground-truth series to check against, which is\nexactly why they’re absent from every approach compared here, not only\nthis project’s.","position":{"start":{"line":175,"column":1},"end":{"line":175,"column":1}},"key":"FWQ67sS2Kj"}],"key":"gG8UkpV9Vb"}],"key":"SjpeC51smp"}],"key":"f0DUoh0qTh"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"next":{"title":"Wind bias-correction replication: milestone 1","url":"/notebooks/replicate-wind-bias-correction","group":"Wind bias-correction replication"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3000"}